    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix thread-unsafe access in nasIntegrityAlgorithm function\n\n### Summary\nThere is a thread-unsafe access to global or shared variable without proper synchronization downstream of function nasIntegrityAlgorithm in openair3/NAS/TEST/AS_SIMULATOR/nas_data.c. When calling nasIntegrityAlgorithm() the behavior is not what is expected. The issue may be in nasIntegrityAlgorithm or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/TEST/AS_SIMULATOR/nas_data.c`: Modified nasIntegrityAlgorithm to make a local copy of the bit field value before comparisons to avoid potential race conditions with concurrent access to the shared structure.\n\nThe function now reads the bit field value once into a local variable and uses that for all comparisons, eliminating potential thread-safety issues when the input structure is accessed concurrently by multiple threads.\n\nTo reproduce the issue, run the AS simulator in a multithreaded environment where multiple threads might access the same NasSecurityAlgorithms structure concurrently. The function may return inconsistent results or cause memory access violations in rare cases due to race conditions during bit field access.\n"
}